snippet.textDisplay: I remember when I was young, I wrote a song that had a very similar melody to a song Hannah Montana sang later. (who said) My sister wanted me to sue Miley (even though she didn't write the song) but I knew there was no way Miley or Billy would have known about it. We didn't post it on the internet or anything. In fact things like this happen all the time. Written language has multiple origins, the telephone was invented twice without either person knowing about the other, and Dennis the Menace is the name of two comics, and they didn't know about the other. I'm sure there's a word for this, but I don't know what.
